<title>USA: Classic Sports Network gets $20 mln investment.</title>
<headline>Classic Sports Network gets $20 mln investment.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1996-09-03</dateline>
<text>
<p>Classic Sports Network Inc said on Tuesday that Warburg Pincus Ventures LP has agreed to invest $20 million in the company and serve on the board of directors.</p>
<p>Classic Sports Network, which airs moments from sports history over cable and direct satellite channels, counts Allen &amp; Co, AT&amp;T Corp, and Wayne Huizenga, the owner of three professional sports teams in Florida, among its investors.</p>
<p>It could not immediately be determined how much of a stake was obtained by the $20 million investment.</p>
